<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><song><author>Converse, Charles Crozat (1834-1918), Scriven, Joseph Medlicott (1819-1886)</author>
<hymn_number>62</hymn_number>
<lyrics>[V1]
 1. Isu, I guolpha a hihzie,
 Gitloh, lungkham cheng paw di'n!
 Hun pha I neihzie pauchama,
 Thil cheng Pathien atun di'n!
 Aw, muonna I mansak zing ui,
 Aw, nat thawk loh ding I thuok,
 Thil cheng I tutloh ziek ahi,
 Pauchamna'n Pathien kawmah!

[V2]
 2. Patepna, thepna I tuok um?
 Khawi ale buoina 'um em?
 I lungdawn ngeiloh diu ahi,
 Pauchamna'n Lalpa hilh in!
 Ziebang Guol ginum I muu em,
 Lungkham cheng ei thawkpih ding?
 Isu'n I hatlohnau A he'i,
 Pauchamna'n Lalpa hilh in!

[V3]
 3. Hatlo leh gikpuo'n I um um,
 Thil ngaihtuohna'n I buoi um?
 Hukdampa I bitnau ahi,
 Pauchamna'n Lalpa hilh in!
 Na guolte'n a hun musit um?
 Pauchamna'n Lalpa hilh in;
 A ban in hun tu'n hun lieh ding,
 Lungmuonna ziechun mun lau!</lyrics>
<title>WHAT A FRIEND WE HAVE IN JESUS</title>
</song>